<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-10-14T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-10-14T22:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7748: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-15T11:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">October 15,
                                        1926—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 15—3: 50
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>481. My 472, October 12, 5 p.m. Following from American consul general,
                            Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“October 14, 3 p.m. French gunboat <hi rend="italic">Alerte</hi>
                                    fired upon yesterday near Wusüeh, killing one sailor, seriously
                                    injuring another. <hi rend="italic">Alerte</hi> fired upon again
                                    below Hankow this morning but no casualties. Fire returned both
                                    times.</p>
                                <p>Conditions at Wuchang continue to improve. Shops are opening and
                                    food supplies ample. About 400 bodies inside and outside walls
                                    in crude coffins now awaiting burial. All Northern troops
                                    evacuated.</p>
                                <p>No change in the situation at Kiukiang.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>